      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In the context of a research position at a university, Text A is generally considered more intelligent and competent. This is because it is written in formal academic English, adhering to standard linguistic conventions, grammatical structures, and vocabulary typically used in academic writing. Its clarity, precision, and use of technical terms (e.g., \"empirical evidence\") convey expertise and familiarity with the subject matter. Text B, on the other hand, uses less formal language, colloquial expressions, and simplified sentence structures that may be perceived as less conventional or even unprofessional in a research setting.",
